1. to put (into); to put away (in); to put back (in); to keep (in); to store (in); to restore (to its place) 書類は全部テープでくくられて金庫におさめられた。All the papers were taped up and kept in the safe.
2. to include (in an anthology, catalogue, etc.); to contain; to publish (in); to capture (on film) Only applies to 収めるその事典は約５０万語の単語を収めている。The dictionary contains about half a million words.
3. to achieve (results, success, etc.); to obtain; to get; to gain; to win; to make (a profit) Only applies to 収めるそのアメリカ映画は大成功を収めた。That American movie was a great success.
4. to pay (fees, taxes, etc.); to deliver; to supply Only applies to 納める資産家は高額の所得税を納めなければならない。A man of wealth has to pay a lot of income tax.
5. to accept (a gift or money)
6. to keep (within a limit)
7. to offer (to a shrine, deity, etc.); to dedicate
8. to subdue; to suppress; to settle See also 治める彼が仲裁してその場は丸く収めた。He intervened and settled the matter peacefully for the time being.
9. to finish; to conclude; to wind up; to bring to a close Only applies to 納める
納める 【おさめる】

3. garbage collection; waste collection Only applies to 収集私たちのゴミは週３回収集されます。Our garbage is collected three times a week.
